Freeland, Respondent, v. Bacon, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. January 17, 1890.) Appeal from city court, general term.

Argued before Larremore, C. J., and Bischoff, J.

W. H. Gibson, for appellant. T. D. Kenneson, for respondent.

No opinion. Ordered that the judgment be affirmed, with costs. For former report, see 7 N. Y. Supp. 674.
